12 An Act relating to public health and safety;
directing hospitals and health care facilities to
13 post certain signage; stating signage requirements;
directing hospitals and health care facilities to
14 develop certain protocols and procedures; directing
the State Department of Health to promulgate rules;
15 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
16
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-114.4 of Title 63, unless
22 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. Upon the effective date of this act, every hospital and
24 health care facility in this state shall be required to post
HB3287 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

CORRECTED
1 dome stic violence and human trafficking signage in inconspicuous
2 areas throughout the hospital and health care facility and in areas
3 deemed private and restricted for the use of patients and healthcare
4 providers only. The signage shall contain the following
5 information:
6 "If you are a victim of domestic abuse or if you are being
7 forced or have been forced to perform any sexual act or are a victim
8 of human trafficking, please notify the staff of this facility
9 immediately."
10 B. Hospitals and health care facilities shall develop protocols
11 and procedures to be used for reporting alleged or confirmed cases
12 of domestic abuse and human trafficking for commercial sex to
13 appropriate law enforcement agencies if requested to do so by the
14 victim prior to discharge of the victim from the hospital or release
15 from a health care facility. The protocols shall also include
16 procedures for assisting law enforcement and the victim of domestic
17 abuse or human trafficking in securing said discharge or release
18 without interference by or notification to the alleged perpetrator
19 of domestic abuse or human trafficking.
20 C. The State Department of Health shall make the signage
21 available for print on the public website of the Department.
22 Hospitals and health care facilities may request that the signage be
23 mailed to the hospital or health care facility for the cost of
24 printing and first class postage.
